<font color="#FF0000">THANKS, HEAPS, DERRICK</font><br>
<tt>Fri Jul 18  0:38:58 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
patriot 692, Derrick<br><br>
Thank you so much for your kind note.  I am extremely pleased that someone has finally recognized what the war in Vietnam was all about, freedom.  I am sure grateful that someone has finally given me a note of thanks for my service in Vietnam.<br><br>
It sure is great that someone finally recognizes that by planting the old Stars and Stripes in Saigon that American Freedom flourished, if only for a short time, in Vietnam.<br><br>
Flourished might be an understatement, because under Thieu and Ky a great many leaders used their freedom to acquire a great deal of wealth.  Is'nt that the American ideal?  Freedom also expanded the wealth of the middle and lower classes who were able to participate in a booming trade in various items.  Bars, Nightclubs, Entertainment and Dancing Clubs, Dating Services, Pharmaceutical outlets, Herbal Medicine outles and various other business really got the cash flowing during the brief period American Freedom flourished, not only in Saigon, buy throughout Vietnam.<br><br>
Our adversaries on the other hand, a ruthless bunch of thugs, were interested in only expanding the power of the communistic world.  The thugs managed, through brain washing and other sinful tactics, to convince the general population that they were only continuing an age old fight to liberate their country.  How deceitful they were.  They must have gotten all their orders directly from Peking or Moscow.  We were never able to convince the general population of the advantages of American style Freedom, Capitalism and Penicillin.  <br><br>
Thank God you know the value of freedom, and particularly good old American Style Freedom.  As we did in Vietnam, I hope someday that you too can fight for freedom.  Hopefully someday somebody can cook something up just like Vietnam so you and all courageous American Freedom loving folk like you can participate.  <br><br>
This has gotter longer than expected, I guess I just got a little free.  Well thanks again.  I am off to use my freedom to go and protest all those abortion things and boycott Disneyland or is it World.  Those damn women and gays, hell they don't deserve no freedom, thats only reserved for us flag wavin vietnam veteran men folk and good folks like you.  <br>
 <br>
  
